This Vulcan- Hart Kettle is up for bid. This Kettle has been inspected regularly by Hartford Steam Boiler Inspection.

This Kettle is in excellent working condition.

If you would desire to bid on this Kettle you can do so online through Google Forms or you can mail in your bid to: Gwinn Area Community Schools (Kettle Bid) P.O. box 447 Gwinn, MI, 49841 or drop off a bid in a sealed envelope at Gwinn High School 50 W. M-35.

Bid Form: https://forms.gle/uBmuzJTWo81A8TKr8

Please make sure you mark the envelope (Kettle Bid).

If you have more questions or would like to look at this Kettle please contact Scott at 906-346-0304. All bids must be in by Thursday August 13th at 12:00 PM.

60 Gallon Vulcan-Hart Self Contained Kettle

Kettle Capacity: 60 Gallons
Kettle Material: Stainless Steel
Heating Source: Electric
Drive Motor: No
Kettle Cover: Hinged
Kettle Outlet(s): 1 Outlet
Kettle Outlet Inside Diameter(s): 2 Inches
Kettle Outlets: Side
Voltage: 208
Phase: 3Ph

We hope to see you there!

post_text: Congratulations, Nicole Sheltrow!! GACS Teacher of the Year!! 💛🖤💛🖤
shared_text:
Gwinn Area Community Schools
May 14 at 8:10 PM ·

Congratulations to Mrs. Nicole Sheltrow, our GACS Teacher of the Year! Mrs. Sheltrow has been a GACS teacher for 20 years and is currently a Title I teacher at Gilbert Elementary School. She is recognized for her leadership among her peers, her teaching strategies to increase student academic skills, and her genuine compassion and high expectations she sets for her students. We surprised her today with a drive-by at the school! Pictured here are her children as well as several of her colleagues.

Barbie Ward-Thomas‎KI Sawyer Elementary School - GACS
May 13 at 11:38 AM ·

Hello Friends and Families surrounding Gwinn Michigan.
We are still serving meals for all kids, 18 years or younger, Monday (for Mon & Tues), Wednesday (for Wed & Thursdsay), Friday (for Friday, Sat, and Sunday!)
Serving starts at 11:00 and runs until 12:00 at KIS & GHS.
As for right now we will be running at least until the end of the first week of June...That is June 5th. We may be serving longer based on the govt. support.
Please Please Please share this info with all of your friends and families...IF WE DON'T USE THIS PROGRAM WE WILL LOSE THIS PROGRAM!
The numbers are all pretty inconsistent at GHS. We want to help but we need your support to make this happen. Please understand even if you "don't" believe you "need" this it will still be availabe, so let us help you and then you can help the program! WIN-WIN!!!!
If you have any questions, concerns or considerations, please email me at bward@gwinn.k12.mi.us
See you soon, I hope!

Spring Photos have arrived!

Below are the days and times this week that parents can come to school to pick up their orders. Please come to the Bus Canopy entrance:

** Tuesday - April 14th: 1:00 to 3:00 p.m.

** Thursday - April 16th: 10:00 a.m to Noon

Attached is a letter that was enclosed in the box explaining the delay of mugs and water bottles. I have made arrangements for these orders to be shipped to my home address once they are complete.

If you have any questions, please let me know.

PS - I will also schedule a day with a later time for those parents who cannot get to school until after regular business hours. Stay tuned!

shared_text:
Forsyth Township
March 14 at 9:04 AM ·

With profound sadness; Late last night, Forsyth Township Firefighter Ben Lauren was killed in the Line of Duty, fighting a structural fire side by side with his FTFD Family. Ben's Father Ron and Sister Tori are also members of the Department, and we ask that you keep them, the whole Lauren Family, and all of our brave volunteers close in your thoughts and prayers. Ben, a 3rd generation Volunteer Firefighter, via his maternal Grandfather, was born on Flag Day (June 14th) 1996, and attended his first of many UP Firefighter's Tournament six weeks later... He was a proud, dedicated and exceptional member of your Fire Department, and was truly the finest representation of our Community's young people - respected and admired by all who knew him.
RIP Ben Lauren, FTFD, GHS class of '14. HERO

February 18 at 5:31 PM ·

LUNCH SERVER NEEDED

Gwinn Area Community Schools is seeking candidates for one (1) part-time lunch server at Gwinn Middle/High School.

Position is two hours/day (11:30 am until 1:30 pm, Monday-Friday) with a starting pay of $11.35/hour.

Applicants must meet all school board requirements and pass a criminal background check. Serve Safe certification is required along with the ability to lift 30-50 pounds.

Interested candidates should apply by submitting a letter of interest and completed application (available at www.gwinn.k12.mi.us) to: Barbie Ward-Thomas, Food Service Director, PO Box 447, Gwinn, MI 49841. Applications are due Friday, February 28, 2020 or until position is filled.

shared_text:
Negaunee High School Booster Club
February 4 at 9:01 PM ·

As many of you know, Gwinn Area Community Schools unexpectedly lost their head football coach and a pillar in their community last month. Touching many lives not only on the field, but off it as well. A mentor to all he coached and someone who made a difference in the community at large.

To honor his legacy and the family he leaves behind, we will be donating our portion of the 50/50 drawing from our boys basketball game against Gwinn this Friday to the Dion Brown family account at Honor Credit Union.

Typically, our 50/50 is how we fund our Booster Club scholarships, however, sometimes there are special circumstances such as this. His passion for athletics, community, the kids he coached and making a difference in the lives of those that knew him will be remembered by all.

Important Athletic Update: First, we've been able to move our high school boys basketball game, originally on 1/30/2020, to FRIDAY, JANUARY 31ST. Also, our Student Council is going to use this week starting on Monday, January 27th as Snow Fest Week which replaces our typical winter homecoming. The week will still include dress-up days along with other activities and a short assembly on Friday. There will also be a dance but we are waiting to hear if the Junior Class will be offering that on Friday night or a different date. Certain things like hall decorating and crowning a king and queen along with assembly games will not take place. Stay tuned and please help to spread the word about the new date for our high school boys basketball game versus Bark River-Harris. GO MODELTOWNERS!

Gwinn PawPacks
January 15 at 1:55 PM ·

LOOK! LOOK! Paw Packs has a big announcement!!

Our favorite Dr Buck at Northern Trails was chatting with James Mennell, owner of Biogenic Reagents on an airplane. Next thing I know Mr. Mennell sent our backpack program over $5,000!!!! Only a little over a year ago our program started. I never would have dreamed of such a generous donation. THANK YOU Jim!

More in the article below, written by the delightful Christie Bleck.

THANK YOU to everyone in this wonderful story for feeding our children!!

To all of our teachers, THANK YOU for taking time out of your classroom to bring your students down to shop! We appreciate your time and support!

A HUGE thank you to the amazing elementary school staff who came on their own down time to help our students shop as well; Marci, Krista, Melissa, Connie, Kimberly and Kimberly.

Another successful Santas Secret Shop has occurred because of all of the wonderful support that has been given to the PTO...

...Parents a very important part of that success is you! Thank you! Thank you for allowing your children to shop at Santas Secret Shop!

Good Evening Everyone 😊

I hope everyone has had a wonderful weekend!

Tomorrow and Tuesday will be Santa Secret Shop in Room 12! All classrooms will be stopping in to shop and please don’t forget to send in the money envelope with your little one! Your little one having the money envelope with them and completed will help our amazing volunteer Santa shoppers! (I added an example envelope below)

Prices this year do vary from $.50- $6.00, so please keep that in mind while filling out your envelope 🙂

We will be accepting Cash or Checks made out to K I Sawyer PTO.

If you have any questions, please ask 🙂

post_text:
Gwinn Area Community Schools have 4 buses up for bid.

2001 - 01B - 57,000 miles not sure about accuracy because the speedometer has been replaced. It will drive away under its own power however it does need a fuel lift pump and it will not pass state inspection.

2002 - 02C - 205,000 miles. It will drive away on its own power however it will not pass state inspection.

2002 - 02D - 180,000 miles has a blown turbo and should be towed away. Not recommend to try and drive under own power.

2004 - 04A - 207,000 miles. Will drive away on its own power however it does have a leaking radiator and the fuel tank does leak. Will not pass state inspection.

· Bids must be in by Monday, October 21st at 10am

· You may stop by the bus garage for inspection

· To talk with Neil during inspection you must stop by Friday, October 18th between 10am and 2pm

· After approval of bid buses must be removed from premises no later than October 25th
